article_title: Glitchtastic! Safari web browser reportedly couldn’t verify Covered California’s server – twitchy.com
article_text:
California’s Obamacare administrators can’t spell, don’t speak English correctly, and think “Asian” is a language.

On top of all that, this photo (brought to our attention yesterday by Twitter [email protected] ) appeared to show an incompatibility between Covered California’s website and Safari’s mobile web browser.

Everything seems to be working fine this afternoon. In any case, Safari browsers account for “only” about three-fifths of all mobile web traffic. No biggie!

Update:

This isn’t the first time someone had problems using Safari:
